{
  "stem": "1975.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 58.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had even some leaders from the Zionist movement who came to our-- to our country, and who tried to explain to us the importance of having our own country, our own state.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But unfortunately, we have-- we didn't have the time to accomplish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some people went to Israel, but most of them felt so secure in Lithuania in the sense that anti-Semitism was not so strong.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this maybe was the reason why we felt that Lithuania is a good place to live.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we had not seen, actually, the handwriting on the wall.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, the borders were not open.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Lithuania was-- I mean, to emigrate, to go to Israel at that time, it was quite difficult.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You have to go through many procedures and through a long process in order to leave Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Part of Lithuania was occupied by Russians.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1939.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As you know, I used to live in Kaunas, because I started in Kaunas.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And during the summer time, after school was finished, after the end of the school year, I used to go back to my family and spend summers in my native city with my friends, and so on.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] This was basically the way I-- I grew up part in Kaunas and part in Rakiszki with my family.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We have noticed and we felt that something is going on when the relations between Germany and Russia have started to come up in the newspapers, the articles about their approach.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we have seen and felt that the proximity of Germany to Lithuania, which was just a matter of hours, we start feeling that there is some kind of danger, and something that might be affecting us.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
